&lt;h1&gt;Senior Paid Advertising Strategist&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About Reunion Marketing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reunion Marketing is a dynamic, data-first digital marketing agency specializing in the automotive industry. We help clients grow through measurable, performance-driven strategies, innovative campaign execution, and a commitment to continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Reunion, data beats intuition. We believe strong paid media performance requires more than technical campaign management. It requires strategic thinking, proactive communication, confident client leadership, and the ability to turn insights into action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Paid Advertising Strategist&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;who can lead high-impact paid search and paid social strategies, influence client outcomes, and help elevate the overall performance standard of our paid advertising team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Paid Advertising Strategist will own and lead paid advertising strategy for a portfolio of client accounts, with responsibility for campaign performance, strategic recommendations, budget management, client communication, and cross-functional alignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for a seasoned paid media professional who is equally comfortable analyzing data, building campaign strategy, presenting performance insights, and influencing client direction. You will serve as a trusted performance advisor for your accounts and help guide clients toward decisions that improve measurable results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not simply an execution-focused role. The Senior Paid Advertising Strategist is expected to think ahead, identify opportunities, solve complex performance challenges, mentor others, and contribute to the continued evolution of Reunion Marketing’s paid advertising approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Paid Media Strategy &amp;amp; Performance Ownership&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own paid advertising strategy, execution, optimization, and performance outcomes across a portfolio of client accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage campaigns across platforms such as Google Ads, Microsoft Ads, Meta, and other relevant paid media channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate client goals into clear paid media strategies, campaign structures, testing plans, and performance benchmarks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor budgets, pacing, conversion trends, lead quality, cost efficiency, and overall account health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify risks, performance gaps, and growth opportunities before they become client concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make proactive recommendations to improve results, increase efficiency, and strengthen client ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead campaign testing initiatives, including audience strategy, creative testing, bidding strategies, landing page recommendations, and conversion optimization opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Client Communication &amp;amp; Strategic Influence&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a senior subject matter expert on client-facing calls, performance reviews, and strategic planning discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex campaign data into clear, compelling performance narratives that clients can understand and act on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidently explain strategy, results, recommendations, and tradeoffs to clients and internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence client decision-making by using data, industry insight, and performance trends to support recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Client Success team members to ensure paid advertising strategy aligns with client goals, expectations, and broader account strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support client retention and growth by demonstrating measurable value and strategic leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
